2.01	The_Sun_Has_Got_His_Hat_On	The Sun Has Got His Hat On	The Sun Has Got His Hat On is one of the main songs in the musical Me and My Girl. It was written by Noel Gay and Ralph Butler, and recorded in 1932 by two popular UK Dance Bands - Ambrose and his Orchestra, with vocals by Sam Browne and by the Henry Hall BBC Dance Orchestra with vocals by Val Rosing .	
